            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'en'" x-cloak>
                <h2>This Week's Observation: Cold Launch Cycles Are Quietly Extending</h2>
<p>This week, multiple overseas teams operating on TikTok Shop reported that the order generation cycle for new products has significantly lengthened compared to last month. A home goods category seller noted that previously, testing with 15 creatives for 5 days would yield stable ROI, but now the same number of creatives requires 7-8 days to confirm creative performance. The platform algorithm's initial traffic support window for new product creatives has shortened, with initial exposure per creative decreasing by approximately 20%-30%.</p>
<p>This means the logic of new product cold launches is shifting from "fast testing, fast decisions" to "accumulation and preparation." The depth of your creative inventory directly impacts whether new products can successfully navigate the cold launch period.</p>
<h2>Problem Diagnosis: Three Typical Manifestations of Insufficient Creative Inventory</h2>
<p><strong>1. Single Testing Dimension, Missing Potential Creatives</strong></p>
<p>Some teams habitually test with 3-5 main creatives repeatedly. If these creatives show average CTR performance, they fall into a vicious cycle of "poor creatives → low conversions → limited reach → slow data accumulation." In reality, the cold launch phase requires multi-dimensional creative testing simultaneously, including product usage scenarios, comparison demonstrations, user pain points, review content, and other various formats. A sufficiently large creative pool increases the probability of finding winning creatives.</p>
<p><strong>2. Stale Creative Update Rhythm</strong></p>
<p>The cold launch period typically requires uploading 1 new creative daily or every two days, continuously replenishing fresh blood. However, in actual operations, the operations team often decides whether to change creatives only after 3-5 days of testing, missing the optimal optimization window. The platform has implicit weightings for creative freshness during cold launch, with new creatives receiving additional initial traffic support.</p>
<p><strong>3. Creative Specifications Mismatched with Placement</strong></p>
<p>TikTok Shop's traffic entrances are diverse, including in-feed ads, marketplace search, creator showcase windows, and other different scenarios. CTR differences for the same product creative across different placements can reach 2-3 times. Some teams find vertical videos perform well in in-feed testing but overlook the conversion advantages of 1:1 square creatives in marketplace scenarios.</p>
<h2>This Week's Recommendations: Reasonable Creative Inventory Strategy for Cold Launches</h2>
<h3>Creative Pool Scale Reference</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Cold Launch Phase</th>
<th>Recommended Creative Count</th>
<th>Update Frequency</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Days 1-3</td>
<td>12-15</td>
<td>3-5 new daily</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Days 4-7</td>
<td>20-25 cumulative</td>
<td>Retain Top 5, eliminate rest</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Days 8-14</td>
<td>Focus on 5-8</td>
<td>Minor adjustments every 2 days</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>Creative Type Mix Recommendations</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Product Showcase (40%)</strong>: Core feature demonstrations, functional comparisons</li>
<li><strong>Scene Immersion (30%)</strong>: Real usage scenarios, emotional resonance</li>
<li><strong>Trust Endorsement (20%)</strong>: Reviews, user testimonials, factory sourcing</li>
<li><strong>Promotional Hook (10%)</strong>: Limited-time offers, stock scarcity</li>
</ul>
<h3>Practical Checklist</h3>
<ol>
<li>Confirm creatives are uploaded to Assets library with normal status</li>
<li>Check if creatives cover 9:16, 1:1, and 16:9 specifications</li>
<li>Verify if the first 3 seconds have subtitles and visual appeal</li>
<li>Cross-check CTA button copy consistency with landing page</li>
<li>Confirm targeting timezone aligns with target market</li>
</ol>
<h2>Operations Reminder</h2>
<p>This week, platform review speeds showed slight fluctuations, with some creatives experiencing delayed launch. It is recommended to upload creatives 24 hours in advance to allow review buffer time. Also monitor account balance status—cold launches consume quickly, and it is recommended to maintain a balance of 1.5 times the estimated consumption to avoid creative interruptions due to insufficient funds.</p>
<p>Creative inventory building is the foundational work of new product cold launches. This week's changes remind us: inventory volume determines testing depth, and testing depth determines optimization space. In the context of intensifying platform traffic competition, the competition for "ammunition sufficiency" has become even more critical.</p>
